      Description = "The initial launch was similar to Artemis I as SLS lofts Orion into space. With crew aboard this mission, Orion and the upper stage, called the interim cryogenic propulsion stage (ICPS), orbited Earth twice to ensure Orion's systems are working as expected while still close to home. Orion started in an elliptical orbit that was refined to a \"safe\" high Earth orbit of approximately 44,525 x 115 statute miles."
    },
    {
