      Description = "On flight day six of Artemis II, the Orion spacecraft and its four-person crew flew around the far side of the Moon on a free-return trajectory. Orion reached closest approach at about 4,067 miles above the lunar surface, using the Moon's gravity to bend its path back toward Earth. The flyby marked the first crewed Artemis mission around the Moon and set a new human spaceflight distance record before the crew began the return trip home.",
